facts.value:
Obituary:  Elmo Philomon Humphreys, age 80 of Springville died June 6, 1993 in Springville.  He was born August 16, 1912 in Ovid, Bear Lake, Idaho to George Albert and Delilah Ann Lindsay Humphreys.  He married Amy Louise Blackburn on April 3, 1935 in the salt Lake L D S Temple.  He was an active member of the LDS church.  He served as Bishop, Stake President, High Councilor, and as a Stake Mission President in Reno Nevada.  He served a mission with his wife in the Washington DC mission from 1984 to 1986.  There he served as director of the Washington D.C. Visitors Center.  He also served as Patriarch in the Hobble Creek Stake in Springville, Utah.  He was the owner of Humphreys Furniture COmpany in Reno, Nevada.  He served as a temple worker until the time of his death.
               He is survived by his wife, Amy Louise, of Springville: tow daughters and one son:  Mrs. Roger(Karen) Olson of Springville;  Glenn Elmo Humphreys of Idaho Falls, Idaho;  Mrs. Howard (Melissa) Anderson of West Jordan;  one sister, Mrs. Giles L. (Floral) Vanerhoof of Antioch, California;  24 grandchildren, and four great grandchildren.  He was preceded in death by one grandson, George Albert Humphreys.  Funeral will be Thurs, June 10, at 11 a.m. in the Hobble Creek 5th ward chapel.  1100 Canyon Road.  Friends may call at the Wheeler Mortuary, 211 E. 200 S. on Wednesday from 6 to 8 p.m. or Thursday from 9:30 to 10:30 a.m.   Burial will be in the Springville Evergreen Cemetery.
